<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1735,2013]" pageId="1" pageNumber="114">
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Weise" authorityYear="1895" box="[151,238,1736,1759]" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" genus="Diomus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="114" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,238,1736,1759]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="114">Diomus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the most speciose genus in the tribe 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gordon" authorityYear="1999" box="[682,775,1735,1760]" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="114" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Diomini">Diomini</taxonomicName>
<bibRefCitation box="[783,943,1735,1760]" pageId="1" pageNumber="114" refId="ref4197" refString="Gordon, R. (1999) South American Coccinellidae (Coleoptera), Part VI: A systematic revision of the South American Diomini, new tribe (Scymninae). Annales Zoologici, Warsaw, 49, 1 - 219." type="journal article">Gordon, 1999</bibRefCitation>
, and possibly the largest genus in the entire family 
<taxonomicName authority="Latreille, 1807" authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1807" box="[230,555,1772,1797]" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="114" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Coccinellidae Latreille, 1807</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation box="[569,826,1772,1797]" pageId="1" pageNumber="114" refId="ref4716" refString="Pang, H. &amp; Slipinski, A. (2009) Revision of the Australian Coccinellidae (Coleoptera). Genus Diomus Mulsant. Part 1. Annales Zoologici, 59, 641 - 698. https: // doi. org / 10.3161 / 000345409 x 485008" type="journal article">Pang &amp; Ślipiński 2009</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation box="[837,898,1772,1796]" pageId="1" pageNumber="114" refId="ref4765" refString="Pang, H. &amp; Slipinski, A. (2010) Revision of the Australian Coccinellidae (Coleoptera). Genus Diomus Mulsant. Part 2. Annales Zoologici, 60, 493 - 545. https: // doi. org / 10.3161 / 000345410 X 550382" type="journal article">2010</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Weise" authorityYear="1895" box="[915,1002,1773,1796]" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" genus="Diomus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="114" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[915,1002,1773,1796]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="114">Diomus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was originally placed as a subgenus of 
<taxonomicName authority="Kugellan, 1794" authorityName="Kugellan" authorityYear="1794" box="[151,440,1807,1832]" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" genus="Scymnus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="114" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,249,1808,1831]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="114">Scymnus</emphasis>
Kugellan, 1794
</taxonomicName>
, and classified, until recent times, in the tribe 
<taxonomicName box="[993,1101,1807,1832]" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="114" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Scymnini">Scymnini</taxonomicName>
Mulsant, 1846 along with a miscellaneous assortment of other small pubescent lady beetles. 
<bibRefCitation box="[889,1058,1844,1869]" pageId="1" pageNumber="114" refId="ref4197" refString="Gordon, R. (1999) South American Coccinellidae (Coleoptera), Part VI: A systematic revision of the South American Diomini, new tribe (Scymninae). Annales Zoologici, Warsaw, 49, 1 - 219." type="journal article">Gordon (1999)</bibRefCitation>
recognized 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Weise" authorityYear="1895" box="[1199,1286,1845,1868]" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" genus="Diomus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="114" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1199,1286,1845,1868]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="114">Diomus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and allies as deserving of their own tribe 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gordon" authorityYear="1999" box="[474,570,1879,1904]" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="114" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Diomini">Diomini</taxonomicName>
, distinct from 
<taxonomicName box="[736,846,1879,1904]" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="114" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Scymnini">Scymnini</taxonomicName>
, but unfortunately his circumscription of the former included some genera belonging to another tribe—Selvadiini Gordon, 1985 (
<bibRefCitation pageId="1" pageNumber="114" refId="ref5160" refString="Vandenberg, N. J. (2002) Coccinellidae Latreille, 1807. In: Arnett, R. &amp; Thomas, M. (Eds.), American Beetles. Vol. 2. Polyphaga: Scarabaeoidea through Curculionoidea. CRC Press, Boca Raton, FL, pp. 371 - 389." type="book chapter">Vandenberg 2002; Vandenberg &amp; Hanson in review</bibRefCitation>
). A re-circumscription and review of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gordon" authorityYear="1999" box="[778,871,1951,1976]" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="114" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Diomini">Diomini</taxonomicName>
is detailed in Vandenberg and Hanson (in review) and will not be repeated here.
</paragraph>
